SUMMARY:Week 2: Free Cash Flow and Capital Budgeting (JOINT CLASS)
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Free Cash Flow and Capital Budgeting\n\nNote: JOINT CLASS for both Blue and Gold cohorts (irregular time due to spring break — both sections meet together on Monday).\n\nObjectives:\n1. Calculate free cash flow (FCF) from financial statements by adjusting operating income for taxes\, capital expenditures\, and changes in working capital.\n2. Evaluate investment projects by estimating expected cash flows and identifying relevant vs. irrelevant costs.\n3. Construct capital budgeting cash flow forecasts for investment projects using incremental cash flow analysis.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Berk and DeMarzo (6th Ed.)\, Chapter 8\n\nAssignments Due This Week: DeltaTech Case Study (due Fri Mar 27 by 11:59pm)\nDeltaTech Assignment: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9059516\n\nCourse Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-2\nAssignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nStudy.Net Materials: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-2
LOCATION:Chou Hall N100
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
