SUMMARY:Week 3: Investment Decision Rules (Gold Cohort)
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Investment Decision Rules\n\nObjectives:\n1. Apply investment decision rules including Net Present Value (NPV)\, Internal Rate of Return (IRR)\, and Payback Period to evaluate capital projects.\n2. Compare decision rules and explain situations in which different methods may produce conflicting recommendations.\n3. Determine which projects a firm should accept or reject based on value creation principles.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Berk and DeMarzo (6th Ed.)\, Chapter 7\n\nAssignments Due This Week: IntelliDrive Case Study (due Fri Apr 3 by 11:59pm)\nIntelliDrive Assignment: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9059517\n\nCourse Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-3\nAssignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nStudy.Net Materials: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-3
LOCATION:Chou Hall N370
STATUS:CONFIRMED
