SUMMARY:Week 5: Valuing Stocks — DCF (Gold Cohort)
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Valuing Stocks - DCF\n\nObjectives:\n1. Estimate the intrinsic value of a stock using discounted cash flow models (Dividend Discount Model and Free Cash Flow models).\n2. Forecast future cash flows and growth rates required for DCF valuation.\n3. Evaluate how changes in growth\, discount rates\, and assumptions affect stock value estimates.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Berk & DeMarzo (6th Ed.)\, Chapter 9\n\nAssignments Due This Week:\n- Homework 2 due Wed Apr 15 @ 11:59pm\n- Interco Case Study due Fri Apr 17 @ 11:59pm\n\nWeek 5 Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-5\nInterco Assignment: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9059523\nHomework 2: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9006397\nStudy.Net (Interco PDF + Spreadsheet): https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374\nAll Assignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nSyllabus: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/syllabus
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-5
LOCATION:Chou Hall N370
STATUS:CONFIRMED
