SUMMARY:Week 6: Relative Valuation of Stocks (Gold Cohort)
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Relative Valuation of Stocks\n\nObjectives:\n1. Apply relative valuation multiples such as P/E\, EV/EBITDA\, and P/B to estimate a company's value.\n2. Select appropriate comparable firms and interpret differences in valuation multiples across companies.\n3. Evaluate the advantages and limitations of relative valuation compared with DCF methods.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Review Week 5 Chapter 9 and class slides\n\nAssignments Due This Week:\n- Homework 3 due Wed Apr 22 @ 11:59pm\n- Twitter Case Study due Fri Apr 24 @ 11:59pm\n\nWeek 6 Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-6\nTwitter Assignment: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9059525\nHomework 3: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9006399\nStudy.Net (Twitter/Elon Musk PDF + Spreadsheet): https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374\nAll Assignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nSyllabus: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/syllabus
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-6
LOCATION:Chou Hall N370
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
