SUMMARY:Week 7: Statistics Review & Optimal Portfolio Selection (Gold Cohort)
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Statistics Review and Optimal Portfolio Selection\n\nObjectives:\n1. Calculate expected return\, variance\, and standard deviation for individual assets and portfolios.\n2. Explain diversification and correlation and how they affect portfolio risk.\n3. Construct efficient portfolios using mean-variance analysis and interpret the efficient frontier.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Berk & DeMarzo (6th Ed.)\, Chapter 11\n\nAssignments Due: No new assignments due this week\n\nWeek 7 Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-7\nAll Assignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nStudy.Net: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374\nSyllabus: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/syllabus
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-7
LOCATION:Chou Hall N370
STATUS:CONFIRMED
