SUMMARY:Week 9: Capital Structure (Gold Cohort)
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Capital Structure\n\nObjectives:\n1. Explain how firms choose between debt and equity financing and how capital structure affects firm value.\n2. Analyze trade-offs of leverage: tax benefits\, financial distress costs\, and agency considerations.\n3. Evaluate how changes in leverage affect risk\, cost of capital\, and shareholder returns.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Berk & DeMarzo (6th Ed.)\, Chapters 14 & 15\n\nAssignments Due This Week:\n- Homework 5: Wed May 13 @ 11:59pm\n\nWeek 9 Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-9-3\nHomework 5: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9006402\nAll Assignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nStudy.Net: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374\nSyllabus: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/syllabus
